properties.otherAdvice:

properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets - THE ROCKS George St between Hickson Rd AND Lower Fort St
properties.otherAdvice:
Long term special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on George St in The Rocks to accommodate the weekly Rocks Markets.

Clearways will be in effect every weekend from 10pm Friday until 10pm Sunday on the eastern side of George St between Hickson Rd and Lower Fort St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

Road closures will also be in place on weekends for the markets from 4am Saturday until 10pm Sunday on sections on Argyle St, Artherden St, George St, Kendall Lane, Mill Lane and Playfair St.
properties.displayName: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets

properties.publicTransport: Buses may experience some delays, for real-time updates on services visit transportnsw.info/alerts

arrangementAttachments.linkName: Crescent lane closure - Alternative route map

properties.otherAdvice:
One of two northbound lanes are closed on The Crescent approaching City West Link from Johnston St in Annandale.

This lane closure will be in place for around seven weeks while Rozelle Interchange upgrades continue. 

Delays are expected on The Crescent and Johnston St during this period and motorists should use alternative routes to avoid delays.

Use Parramatta Rd for travel to and from the city, and local roads for access to and from Victoria Rd.

Allow plenty of additional travel time, particularly during the morning and afternoon peak periods.

properties.headline: STAY-AT-HOME ORDERS Greater Sydney, Central Coast, Blue Mountains, Wollongong, Shellharbour, Orange, Blayney & Cabonne
properties.otherAdvice:

Stay at home orders are also in place in the Orange City Council, Blayney Shire Council and Cabonne Council areas from Wed 21 July 12:01am to Wed 28 July 12:01am.

Visit nsw.gov.au for more information.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Urgent bridge repairs - MACKSVILLE Giinagay Way on Macksville Bridge over Nambucca River
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
A 22 tonne load limit and single lane restrictions have been placed on the bridge after routine inspections found damage to some structural elements.

The restrictions will remain in place until temporary repair work can be carried out.

Motorists crossing the bridge will also experience delays, with traffic control and a reduced speed limit of 40km/h in place
properties.diversions:
Vehicles of more than 22 tonnes use an alternative route via Giinagay Way
and the Pacific Hwy, which will add about 25 minutes travelling time.
